              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "MAGSP"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The solenoidal HELIOS spectrometer with the",
                "central field of 2T was used for momentum separation",
                "of reaction products."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SI"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Protons from the (d,p) reaction emitted at",
                "forward center-of-mass angles (backwards in the",
                "laboratory) for both 14C and 14N were detected using",
                "the Si array, placed at a distance 125 - 475 mm on axis",
                "and subtending 10 deg < theta(cm) < 40 deg (the",
                "c.m. angle and the detector position along the axis",
                "are related to one another)."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TELES"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Counter telescope located 900 mm from the",
                "target was used as a recoil detector for reaction",
                "trigger and to determine 14C/14N beam ratio."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Inverse kinematics was used"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "A cocktail beam of 14C and 14N was accelerated to 10",
                "MeV/A at a total intensity (14C + 14N) of approximately",
                "300 000 particles per second. A time-averaged ratio",
                "of 1:1 was determined within 3%, or approximately",
                "1.5E+5 particles per second of both 14C and 14N on",
                "average"
              ]
            }
